Class DoubleArraySeq

  • java.lang.Object
    • DoubleArraySeq
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class DoubleArraySeq
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class is a homework assignment; A DoubleArraySeq is a collection of double numbers. The sequence can have a special "current element," which is specified and accessed through four methods that are not available in the bag class (start, getCurrent, advance and isCurrent).
    Version:
    March 5, 2002
    See Also:
    Java Source Code for this class (www.cs.colorado.edu/~main/edu/colorado/collections/DoubleArraySeq.java)

        public DoubleArraySeq()

        Throws:

        Throws:
